# Launcher navigation (frozen intent)

Read **`docs/ENGINEERING.md`** (launcher contract) and **`docs/QA.md`** before changing detail enter/exit, Esc, or keyboard routing.

## Detail exit — always

- User-facing detail exit (Esc, back, close chrome) → **`exitDetailFromChrome()`** — not `closeDetail()` alone.
- `beginDetailMode` / `endDetailMode` / `cancelDetailMode` must stay paired; every exit restores `isEditable`.
- `closeDetail()` is UI teardown only; callers that need query restore must use `exitDetailFromChrome`.

## Detail mode search field

- `beginDetailMode`: suspend query, clear visible field, `isEditable = false`.
- Persist suspended detail queries through `searchBar.persistedQuery`; do not read `stringValue` alone while detail mode clears the visible field.

## Keyboard — do NOT

- Route ↑↓ or ⌘1–9 to hidden list rows while `showingDetail`.
- Advertise ⌘W close detail without implementing it on `LauncherPanel`.
- Rely on `ModuleDetailView.handleKeyDown` via search field only when `activate()` focuses subviews.

## Keyboard — always

- Block Tab / ⌘K action panel open in detail mode (`LauncherKeyRouter`).
- Forward module shortcuts from focused detail subviews or a central panel key dispatcher.
- Action panel arrow keys must work regardless of whether search or list holds focus (audit K7).

## Panel hide

- `hide()` does not tear down detail; document behavior if changing session restore.

## PR requirements

When fixing navigation/shortcut issues: update `docs/ENGINEERING.md`, `docs/MODULES.md`, and `docs/QA.md`.
